<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-11071] Invalidate legacy schema CFSs at startup</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-11071</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ColumnFamilyStore&lt;/tt&gt; instances are created for legacy schema tables at startup when &lt;tt&gt;SystemKeyspace&lt;/tt&gt; is initialized as they may be required for schema migration during upgrade. Before startup completes, the schema info for these is expunged from &lt;tt&gt;system_schema&lt;/tt&gt;, but the &lt;tt&gt;CFS&lt;/tt&gt; instances are not invalidated, which leaves their mbeans registered and visible via nodetool &amp;amp; JMX.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
