                            <comment id="15119182" author="iamaleksey" created="Wed, 27 Jan 2016 12:48:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mikea&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mikea&quot;&gt;mikea&lt;/a&gt; This is just cosmetic, right? I don&apos;t think there was any reason. It&apos;s just a minor oversight.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15119210" author="mike_tr_adamson" created="Wed, 27 Jan 2016 13:16:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=iamaleksey&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;iamaleksey&quot;&gt;iamaleksey&lt;/a&gt; Yes, it fixes an inconsistency between the tables returned by &lt;tt&gt;cqlsh&amp;gt; describe tables;&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;nodetool tablesstats&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
